  "title": "Spreading the greetings of Salam (Peace)",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 225",
  "arabic": "ثَلاَثٌ مَنْ جَمَعَهُنَّ فَقَدْ جَمَعَ الْإِيمَانَ الْإِنْصَافُ مِنْ نَفْسِكَ وَبَذْلُ السَّلاَمِ لِلْعَالَمِ وَالْإِنْفَاقُ مِنَ الإِقْتَارِ",
  "meaning": "Aammar said: ‘Three characteristics, whoever combines them, has completed his faith: to be just, to spread greetings to all people and to spend (charitably) out of the little you have.",
